Episodes.Title: Time Will Tell
Episodes.Plot: In the season two premiere, we pick up right where we left off. MacPherson has blown Artie to smithereens, and disappeared. Is Leena really a traitor? Where has Claudia gone? How will Pete, Myka and the Warehouse fare without Artie? What other havoc did MacPherson wreak when he was alone in the Warehouse? And is there yet a new villain on the horizon?
Episodes.GuestStars: Roger Rees, Jaime Murray, Tyler Hynes

Episodes.Title: Mild Mannered
Episodes.Plot: A super-powered vigilante is at large in Detroit, and the agents try to track down the person responsible. Meanwhile, things between Leena and Claudia are still tense, and Artie is haunted by the spirit of his dead friend.
Episodes.GuestStars: Roger Rees, Sean Maher, Jewel Staite

Episodes.Title: Beyond Our Control
Episodes.Plot: When an artifact meant for the Warehouse turns up in the small town next door, the team finds themselves in the middle of a B-movie meltdown complete with cowboys, gladiators, sci-fi robots and beach storming marines. Their only chance of survival rests with the man who invented television, Philo T. Farnsworth.
Episodes.GuestStars: Paula Garces, Nolan Gerard Funk, Mark A. Sheppard, Philip Winchester, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: Age Before Beauty
Episodes.Plot: When young super models rapidly age 50 years overnight, Pete and Myka go undercover in the glam world of high fashion to discover who ? and what ? is behind the transformations.
Episodes.GuestStars: Tawny Cypress, Phillip Rhys, Nolan Gerard Funk, Salvatore Antonio, Natalie Krill, Robin Kasyanov, Erica Cox, Shauna MacDonald

Episodes.Plot: Douglas Fargo of Eureka's Global Dynamics is sent to Warehouse 13 to help update its aging computer system. This triggers a seemingly sentient computer virus that sends the Warehouse into lockdown and traps the team inside.
Episodes.GuestStars: Neal Grayston, Nolan Gerard Funk, Rene Auberjonois, Paloma Nunez

Episodes.Title: Around the Bend
Episodes.Plot: Mrs. Frederick secretly recruits Pete to find a mole within the organization who is buying artifacts. However, when the mole finds out, they go after those closest to Pete.
Episodes.GuestStars: Tia Carrere, Mark A. Sheppard, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: For the Team
Episodes.Plot: Claudia has just been given her first assignment, but when it involves a real human torch and H.G. Wells could it be too much for her to handle? Not to mention an appearance by an old love of Artie's
Episodes.GuestStars: Jaime Murray, Paula Garces, Lindsay Wagner

Episodes.Title: Merge With Caution
Episodes.Plot: The agents hope to spend a weekend relaxing until an artifact gets in the way.
Episodes.GuestStars: Paula Garces, Laura Harris, Cody Runnels

Episodes.Title: Vendetta
Episodes.Plot: Someone is using Artie's artifacts to commit a series of murders.
Episodes.GuestStars: Tia Carrere, Nolan Gerard Funk, Simon Reynolds, Faran Tahir, Jaime Murray

Episodes.Title: Where and When
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka use H.G. Wells's time machine to travel back to 1961.
Episodes.GuestStars: Roberta Maxwell, Jaime Murray, Armin Shimerman, David Anders

Episodes.Title: Buried (1)
Episodes.Plot: When Mrs. Frederic is stricken ill, the agents must search for a cure before it's too late. Their quest takes them to Egypt and the long-lost Warehouse 2.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jaime Murray, Paula Garces, Mark A. Sheppard, Lindsay Wagner, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: Reset (2)
Episodes.Plot: The team tries to track down their rogue member, and discover the artifact they have is unexpectedly powerful. Meanwhile, Claudia wonders about her future with the Warehouse team and Pete must choose between Kelly and the mission.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jaime Murray, Faran Tahir, Paula Garces, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: Secret Santa
Episodes.Plot: As the Warehouse team prepares to celebrate the holidays in snowy South Dakota, Pete and Myka are called upon to hunt down a malevolent Santa Claus. Meanwhile, in time for Hanukkah, Artie and his estranged father, Isadore Weisfelt reunite after 30 years.
